<subSubSection id="C30A6528FFB1FF83C5BC1804FE4EFA8E" pageId="19" pageNumber="54" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAF36A3FFB1FF83C5BC1804FE4EFA8E" blockId="19.[174,1127,1131,1291]" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">
Taxonomic notes. The widely distributed North American species shows a considerable geographical variation. However, only 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB1FF83C61118E2FDAFFB4D" authority="(Barnes &amp; McDunnough, 1913)" baseAuthorityName="Barnes &amp; McDunnough" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eurois" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="purpurissata" subSpecies="apurpura">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB1FF83C61118E2FBE4FB23" box="[839,1126,1165,1190]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">P. purpurissata apurpura</emphasis>
(Barnes &amp; McDunnough, 1913)
</taxonomicName>
has an allopatric range (
<collectingRegion id="49D4F841FFB1FF83C60818C1FC45FB4C" box="[862,967,1198,1225]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">Arizona</collectingRegion>
), while “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB1FF83C16018C0FD82FB6F" authority="Smith, 1893" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mamestra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="languida">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB1FF83C16018C0FEE7FB6C" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">Mamestra languida</emphasis>
Smith, 1893
</taxonomicName>
” possibly represents a rare hybrid with 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB1FF83C6A718BFFBE5FB6C" box="[1009,1127,1232,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="54" phylum="Nemertea" rank="species" species="nugatis">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB1FF83C6A718BFFBE5FB6C" box="[1009,1127,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">P. nugatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B52FFB1FF83C5BA189EFE42FA8E" author="MCCABE, T. M." box="[236,448,1265,1291]" pageId="19" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 141" refId="ref11622" refString="MCCABE, T. M. (1980): A reclassification of the Polia complex for North America (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae). - New York State Museum, Bulletin No. 432. i - vi, 1 - 141 pp." type="book chapter" year="1980">MCCABE 1980: 24</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
